ts: 43<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/27/01 7:17:43 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Reservation System</span><hr size=1> I have a few ideas i'm going to throw out.<br>
<br>
First, a reservation is for the entire plane and every mob therein with no exceptions.  If a guild can't do the big boss's, then that belongs to the next raid.  If say a guild wants the boss and he's not being taken down, they can be allowed to do the boss but only if there is enough time to allow for a respawn for that next raid that may want the boss.  It's basically this, if a guild/organizer signs up for a plane, they have a right to the boss.  They do not have the right to deal the boss away from another raid.  Any days where that plane is not reserved, those days are FFA or FCFS but mobs are only taken if there is enough time to allow for that mob to respawn for the next reserved raid.<br>
<br>
This should go for Air, Fear and Hate for sure.  I think PoG should be added but i'm open.<br>
<br>
It is the responsibility of each guild/organizer to check the board and this &quot;we never check the board&quot; excuse is so lame and insulting.  <br>
<br>
Sheebla <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umarisscaleblade.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maris Scale Blade</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 20<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/27/01 7:27:28 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.facelink.com/Finrod?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Reservation System</span><hr size=1> I do not feel that PoG should be added to any kind of reservation list, considering how under-utilized it is.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uligarrwiz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ligarr WIZ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Protector of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 331<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/27/01 7:29:36 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   .</span><hr size=1> Only thing about this is that say Cazic will just goto waste alot imo.also if a guild doesnt kill say the broken golem for wiz epic id rather see it killed that night so it spawns again faster and another wiz can get him sooner<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .<br>
<br>
Ligarr just my opinion <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usheebla1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sheebla1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 46<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/27/01 7:41:22 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: .</span><hr size=1> Another way to look at it is that it's FFA as long as you gon't infringe on a reserved raids rights to the mobs there.  Kill anything there to your hearts content, but you better make sure that those mobs will be respawned for the next raid that wants them.  It's just to simple.  And, what you &quot;want&quot;?  What about what others want?<br>
<br>
Sheebla<br>
<br>
Sheebla <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uazzimezzcaline.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Azzi Mezzcaline</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 86<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/27/01 7:47:15 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: .</span><hr size=1> I am of the same opinion as Ligarr. The more times any of the god/epic spawns are dropped it is better for the server. <br>
I do agree with the way I've read that SR and Watchers goes about it. They ask the raid leader and invite those that want to join in on the kill. I don't think Cazic should stay alive for a full month because those in the rotation don't have the power to take him out. I know that's taking it a bit extreme but I'm sure you can see my point.<br>
I know that may sound FFA but not really. The raid leader has a right to invite who they want and when they want them. <br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bbrellserilis.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=kobayashi>Kobayashi</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Usual Suspect</span><br>  Posts: 657<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/27/01 7:53:11 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Hmm</span><hr size=1> The only thing is that its seems silly for a guild to book a whole plane when they literally only need one MOB in the zone.  Alot of stuff is going to start rotting.<br>
<br>
Kobayashi<br>
59th wiz <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umaliken.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maliken</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>All Aboard! Mantrain leaving the station!</span><br>  Posts: 286<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/27/01 7:56:41 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: .</span><hr size=1> Well...My opinion here is no thanks Sheebla...<br>
<br>
Why on earth would we want to see spawns wasted. For example...I head someone who was leading a fear raid say something along the lines of...We are gonna kill ct! I admired the devotion to trying it...But I was not surprised when draco wiped them out TWICE. Simple fact is most people cannot handle the CT spawn yet so putting him as part of a planar reservation is bullcrap. A planar reservation is fine IMO to include everything but the golems, draco and CT for Fear. Not really an issue with Sky since it has not been changed in anyway. And with Hate I would say also Innie would not be part of a plane's reservation.<br>
<br>
Now before you get all hot and bothered and reply with your righteous indignation Sheebla. I want you to really consider. If no one but a few guilds can kill a mob...What is the point on leaving it in a reservation system where it will stay up?<br>
<br>
PS. Personal opinion only :P <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uadunofbrell.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Adun of Brell</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Burn the Witch! [Mod]</span><br>  Posts: 1823<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/27/01 8:17:04 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.pangea.ca/~grinch/ladun.jpg width=67 height=150></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: .</span><hr size=1> Sheeb: This isn't just something that can be declared.  Some sort of guidelines have to be laid down for how the guilds that only need CT &amp; Draco from fear can come in &amp; kill CT &amp; Draco.<br>
<br>
What you're asking is similar to asking that Nagafen be considered as part of a Fire Giant raid, and that Nagafen cannot be killed unless you've got a reservation for Fire Giants.<br>
<br>
What would that do?  You'd have people reserving FG's simply for a shot at Nagafen, and that would get in the way of people who want only to do FG's.<br>
<br>
Bottom line: THE SYSTEM WILL NOT WORK UNLESS EVERYONE FINDS IT ACCEPTABLE.<br>
<br>
Saying that CT &amp; Draco MUST remain up unless SR, or Watchers signs up for the plane &amp; happens to have them up will likely be unacceptable for those guilds.<br>
<br>
On Prexus, the guild Unity has made it known that on a 3 guild rotation, when CT is up, one of those guilds will go into Fear &amp; clear the plane before the reserved raid is scheduled to go in.  Why?  Mostly because people were unwilling to work out something with the guilds that needed only CT &amp; Draco.<br>
<br>
Members of guilds that kill CT &amp; Draco:  What do you see as a good way of sharing the gods? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usheebla1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sheebla1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 47<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/27/01 8:31:47 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   re</span><hr size=1> Did you read the whole thing, guess not by your comments.<br>
